### Steps to do

- Install terraform and aws-cli, set your aws credentials (if you havent already done so)
- Create a terraform project with an aws provider https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs
- Initialize the skeleton of the project using terraform init
- Declare an Amazon SNS topic by referencing https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/aws/latest/docs/resources/sns_topic
- Plan the changes using terraform plan
- Create the topic sing terraform apply
- Observe changes to tfstate file
- Cleanup using terraform destroy
- Observe changes to tfstate file

#### bonus

- Change where to store your tfstate file by declaring a backend block https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/language/settings/backends/s3


### use terraform init when there's changes for:
### -> provider (or location), backend, and module
